OL,3,CGovernment 'failing to keep promise to
OL,4,Cchildren on mental health and housing'
OL,6,FWhile making criticisms on mental
OL,7,Fhealth services and housing, it said
OL,8,F"many strides" were made on education.
OL,10,FThe organisation gave both the early
OL,11,Fchildhood education and care and the
OL,12,Ffree school books scheme a high A
OL,13,Fminus grade.
OL,15,FIn recognition of the sustained
OL,16,Finvestment in the Hot School Meals
OL,17,FProgramme, the Government was awarded
OL,18,Fa B grade for tackling food poverty.
